{"WAMBLE":[{"def":"To heave; to be disturbed by nausea; -- said of the stomach.","pos":""},{"def":"To move irregularly to and fro; to roll.","pos":""}],"WAMBLE-CROPPED":[{"def":"Sick at the stomach; also, crestfallen; dejected.","pos":""}],"WAMMEL":[{"def":"To move irregularly or awkwardly; to wamble, or wabble.","pos":""}],"WAMP":[{"def":"The common American eider.","pos":""}],"WAMPUM":[{"def":"Beads made of shells, used by the North American Indians as money, and also wrought into belts, etc.","pos":""}]}